<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ISO-8859-1" standalone="no"?> 
<!DOCTYPE MAN SYSTEM "../../man.dtd">
<MAN>
  <LANGUAGE>eng</LANGUAGE>
  <TITLE>prod  </TITLE>
  <TYPE>Scilab Function  </TYPE>
  <DATE>April 1993  </DATE>
  <SHORT_DESCRIPTION name="prod"> product  </SHORT_DESCRIPTION>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>y=prod(x)  </CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>y=prod(x,&apos;r&apos;) or y=prod(x,1)  </CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
  <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>y=prod(x,&apos;c&apos;) or y=prod(x,2)  </CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
  </CALLING_SEQUENCE>
  <PARAM>
 <PARAM_INDENT>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>x  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
    : real or complex vector or matrix
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_ITEM>
  <PARAM_NAME>y  </PARAM_NAME>
  <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
    : real or complex scalar or matrix
  </PARAM_DESCRIPTION> 
  </PARAM_ITEM>
 </PARAM_INDENT>
  </PARAM>
  <DESCRIPTION>
  <P>
    For a vector or a matrix <VERB>x</VERB>, <VERB>y=prod(x)</VERB>  returns in the scalar <VERB>y</VERB> the prod of all the entries
    of <VERB>x</VERB>, , e.g. <VERB>prod(1:n)</VERB> is n!
  </P>
  <P>
    <VERB>y=prod(x,&apos;r&apos;)</VERB> (or, equivalently, <VERB>y=prod(x,1)</VERB>)computes the
    rows elementwise product of  <VERB>x</VERB>. <VERB>y</VERB> is the row vector: <VERB>y(i)=prod(x(i,:))</VERB>. 
  </P>
  <P>
    <VERB>y=prod(x,&apos;c&apos;)</VERB> (or, equivalently, <VERB>y=prod(x,2)</VERB>) computes the
    columns elementwise product of  <VERB>x</VERB>. <VERB>y</VERB> is the column vector: <VERB>y(i)=prod(x(:,i))</VERB>. 
  </P>
  <P>
    <VERB>prod</VERB> is not implemented for sparse matrices.
  </P>
  </DESCRIPTION>
  <EXAMPLE><![CDATA[
A=[1,2;0,100];
prod(A)
prod(A,'c')
prod(A,'r')
 ]]></EXAMPLE>
  <SEE_ALSO>
    <SEE_ALSO_ITEM> <LINK>sum</LINK> </SEE_ALSO_ITEM>     <SEE_ALSO_ITEM> <LINK>cumprod</LINK> </SEE_ALSO_ITEM>
  </SEE_ALSO>
</MAN>
